# CSS Basics üé®

**CSS** (Cascading Style Sheets) is used to style and layout web pages.

## Why CSS?
- **HTML** = Skeleton (Structure)
- **CSS** = Skin & Clothes (Presentation)

## Syntax

```css
selector {
  property: value;
}
```

```css
h1 {
  color: blue;
  font-size: 24px;
}
```

# More Selectors üåü

## Universal Selector (*)
Selects EVERYTHING.
```css
* {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
}
```

## Grouping Selectors
Apply same style to multiple selectors.
```css
h1, h2, p {
  font-family: Arial;
}
```

## Descendant Selector
Space separates ancestor and descendant.
```css
div p { color: red; }
/* Selects only <p> inside <div> */
```
